import pandas as pd

ercot = pd.read_excel("/Users/alinahasan/Downloads/ERCOT_Merged_ENERGY.xlsx")

# Convert Hour Ending to string
he = ercot['Hour Ending'].astype(str)

# Identify 24:00 rows
mask_24 = he.str.contains(r"\s24:00$", regex=True)

# Replace 24:00 -> 00:00
he_fixed = he.str.replace(r"\s24:00$", " 00:00", regex=True)

# Parse to datetime
ts = pd.to_datetime(he_fixed, format="%m/%d/%Y %H:%M", errors="coerce")

# Add 1 day where original was 24:00
ts.loc[mask_24] = ts.loc[mask_24] + pd.Timedelta(days=1)

# Assign timestamp
ercot['timestamp'] = ts

# Build final ERCOT load table
ercot = ercot[['timestamp', 'ERCOT']].dropna().set_index('timestamp')
ercot = ercot.rename(columns={'ERCOT': 'ercot_load_mw'})

In[23]:
# temperature-driven demand
df['cooling_degree'] = (df['temp_c'] - 18).clip(lower=0)
df['heating_degree'] = (18 - df['temp_c']).clip(lower=0)

# time controls
df['hour'] = df.index.hour
df['dayofweek'] = df.index.dayofweek
df['month'] = df.index.month

# solar & rain effects
df['solar_exposure'] = df['shortwave_rad'] * df['is_day']
df['is_raining'] = (df['precip'] > 0).astype(int)

hot = hot_day_df.sort_index()

variables = [
    ('ercot_load_mw', 'ERCOT Load (MW)'),
    ('temp_c', 'Temperature (C)'),
    ('wet_bulb_c', 'Wet Bulb (C)'),
    ('dew_point_c', 'Dew Point (C)'),
    ('solar_exposure', 'Solar Exposure'),
    ('wind_speed', 'Wind Speed'),
    ('cloud_cover', 'Cloud Cover (%)'),
    ('pressure', 'Pressure (hPa)')
]

n_cols = 3
n_rows = math.ceil(len(variables) / n_cols)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(
    nrows=n_rows,
    ncols=n_cols,
    figsize=(13, 4 * n_rows),
    sharex=True
)

axes = axes.flatten()

hours = hot.index.hour

for ax, (col, label) in zip(axes, variables):
    ax.bar(hours, hot[col], width=0.8, edgecolor="black", alpha=0.8)
    ax.set_title(label, fontsize=12)
    ax.set_xticks(range(24))           # show 023
    ax.set_xlim(-0.5, 23.5)
    ax.grid(axis="y", alpha=0.3)
    ax.set_xlabel("")
    ax.set_ylabel("")

# turn off unused panels
for ax in axes[len(variables):]:
    ax.axis("off")

# x-label only on bottom row
for ax in axes[-n_cols:]:
    ax.set_xlabel("Hour of Day")

fig.suptitle(
    f"Hottest Day ({hottest_day}): Actual ERCOT Load & Weather (Hourly)",
    fontsize=16,
    y=1.02
)

plt.show()
